humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report indicates that metastatic breast carcinoma was identified in 1 of 16 lymph nodes examined in the right axillary lymph node dissection (part E). This corresponds to N1 stage according to the AJCC staging system.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report indicates that the patient had a right breast simple mastectomy and right axillary lymph node dissection. In the lymph node dissection specimen, metastatic breast carcinoma was identified in 1 out of 16 lymph nodes examined (E9). This corresponds to a pathologic N stage of N1.
